                <h1>Mae C. Jemison: First African American Woman in Space</h1>
                <p>Mae C. Jemison, an American physician and NASA astronaut, made history as the first African American woman to travel in space aboard the Space Shuttle Endeavour in 1992. Beyond her stellar career, Jemison is a passionate advocate for science education and has founded programs to inspire young minds in STEM fields.</p>
